Please implement a normalizer for the PURE lambda-calculus.
Note that a normalizer should go under "lambda" to normalize
the body of a lambda-abstraction. This one requires that you
use 'term_subst1' (vs. 'term_subst0), which handles substitution
for open lambda-terms.

def term_normlz(tm0):
    """
    Please use the leftmost evaluation strategy to normlize
    a given PURE lambda-term
    """

######
#
# Task 3: 20 points
#
######

Recall that the factorial function can be encoded in LAMBDA as
follows:

term_fact = \
term_app(Yv,
term_lam("f", term_lam("n",
  term_ifb(term_op2("<=", tvar_n, tint_0), tint_1,
    term_op2("*", tvar_n, term_app(tvar_f, term_op2("-", tvar_n, tint_1)))))))

term_fact_3 = term_app(term_fact, term_int(3))

Please use the functions implemented in Task~1 to translate it into
an encoding in a PURE lambda-term (of the name term_fact_3_pure). Instead
of using Yv, please use Theta to implement recursion. Please use term_normlz to
normalize term_fact_3_pure and print out the result.

Theta is often referred as Turing fixed-point combinator and it is defined as
follows:

Theta = (lam x.lam y.y(xxy))\ (lam x.lam y.y(xxy))

Like Y, Theta is only good for call-by-name; it has a variant for call-by-value.
